title: Police Investigating Reports Of Attempted Home Larceny
text:
Police Investigating Reports Of Attempted Home Larceny October 19, 2015, 5:43 AM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
Police report that one or more suspects were trying to enter homes and garages near 41st Street and Sertoma Avenue. 
At approximately 12:30 a.m. Monday, Sioux Falls Police were called to the 3800 block of South Morrow Drive. Officers were told a man may have tried to enter a home. He was described as tall, skinny man in a black-hooded sweatshirt. 
Shortly after, a neighbor on West Oriole Circle said they heard someone in their garage. 
Police are advising homeowners to keep doors and vehicles locked, and notify authorities of any suspicious people trying door handles and loitering near vehicles. The investigation is ongoing. It is unknown if anything was taken.
